data.description: Make your escape to this stunning property located on a quiet cul-de-sac in the coveted Stage Run community. Nestled amidst towering trees with breathtaking mountain views, this home checks all the boxes! Step thru the front door & be welcomed by soaring vaulted ceilings & an abundance of natural light streaming through expansive windows. The spacious eat-in kitchen & dining room flow nicely to the great room boasting a gorgeous river rock fireplace. This 4-bedroom residence includes a dedicated office space with a private deck, ideal for remote work. The primary suite offers a peaceful retreat with its own fireplace, private deck & luxurious ensuite bathroom with separate vanity area. Three additional bedrooms ensure plenty of space for family & guests. Entertain effortlessly in the finished basement with bar area & wood stove, or on the spacious Trex deck. Outside, enjoy the spa & outdoor fireplace, the perfect setting for relaxing evenings under the stars. Or perhaps a game of horse shoes?  Other notable features include a new roof, a rare 4th car garage providing ample storage for vehicles & outdoor gear, concrete driveway witha large apron and turn around, front & back irrigation, & a private well & septic ensuring self-sufficiency. Situated on THE premier Stage Run lot, this home offers the ultimate in privacy & tranquility, yet is only 5 minutes from schools & shopping. County-maintained roads & a remarkably low 2.9% tax rate. This property presents a rare opportunity to own a luxury home in an exclusive neighborhood for under $1 million. BE SURE TO LOOK FOR THE VIRTUAL TOUR/VIDEO LINK. Don't miss your chance to experience close-in country living at its finest – schedule a tour today & make this exceptional property your new home! (Floor plans are available in the supplements section). Two Gun Safes and John Deere Tractor lawn mower are negotiable; large gas grill with prep counters included. BUYER/BUYER'S AGENT TO VERIFY ALL INFO.
